    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required gradation levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped as not-assessed per MRL 2 requirements. Validation demonstrates NIH prediction within 15% of experimental data across all operating points. Uncertainty quantification confirms that combined input uncertainty contributes less than 12% variance to predicted RH values, supporting the conclusion that RH < 1 holds robustly across the operating envelope. The credibility assessment team accepts this package in support of the 510(k) submission for the Class II CPB device.",
